	        <strong><span id="speakerNameLabel">Xavier Poix</span></strong>
	        <table border="1" width="100%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
		        <tr>
			        <td valign="top" class="tableCell"><span id="speakerTitleCompanyLabel">Managing Director, Ubisoft Montpellier and Paris Studios (Presenting Red Steel, a Nintendo Revolution exclusive)</span></td>
		        </tr>
		        <tr>
			        <td valign="top" class="tableCell"><span id="speakerBioLabel">As Managing Director of Ubisoft’s Montpellier and Paris studios, Xavier oversees approximately 200 people total between the two studios. Working closely with Michel Ancel in Montpellier, he was producer of Peter Jackson’s King Kong: The Official Game of the Movie. His Paris team recently finished working on Tom Clancy’s Ghost Recon Advanced Warfighter on Xbox 360 and is currently working on the Nintendo Revolution exclusive title, Red Steel.  The Montpellier team is leading development on the recently announced fourth instalment of the Rayman franchise.

Xavier joined Ubisoft in 1998 at the age of 26 after 2 years spent in China. Based in Paris he soon became Sales Director of Ubisoft France before switching positions to manage the Montpellier studio in 2004. End 2005 he was also appointed at the head of the Paris studio. He holds a business degree and is fluent in English and French.
</span></td>
